<subSubSection pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1437,151,934]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,871,897]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species epithet is a Latin adjective combined from ‘Lebu’ (after Lebu Valley) and suffix ‘- 
<emphasis box="[170,195,907,932]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">us</emphasis>
(- 
<emphasis box="[220,234,907,932]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">a</emphasis>
, - 
<emphasis box="[258,292,907,932]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">um</emphasis>
)’ (of or from a place).
</paragraph>
